  "description": "Sylvia Wynter (1928–) is a Jamaican philosopher, cultural theorist, novelist, and former dancer whose work develops a comprehensive critique of the modern Western subject — Man in two successive overrepresentations — and a corresponding demand for a new descriptive statement of the human.",
